title: In the Year of Jubilee
creator: George Gissing
description: Librivox recording of In the Year of Jubilee by George Gissing. Read by skoval. The Jubilee marks the fiftieth year of the reign of Queen Victoria. Dickensian in its sweeping scope of London life, Jubilee depicts the harsh and disreputable conditions of lower-middle class life at the end of the 19th century. (Introduction by S. Kovalchik) For more free audiobooks, or to become a volunteer reader, please visit librivox.org. M4B format available
